article.headline: Wagner 91, Fairleigh Dickinson 63
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- James Ulrich scored 28 points to lead Wagner to a 91-63 victory over Fairleigh Dickinson on Saturday night that gave the Seahawks a berth in the Northeast Conference playoffs. Joey Mundweiler added 17 points for Wagner (11-17, 8-9 Northeast), which led 35-34 at halftime. Jamal Smith added 13 points, and Mark Porter had 11 points and 12 rebounds. Cameron Tyler led the Knights (14-14, 9-8) with 18 points, and Mike Peeples had 13 and Andre Harris 12. After Harris opened the second half with a layup that gave FDU a 37-34 lead, Mundweiler scored eight points, including a pair of 3-pointers, to spark a 20-4 surge that put Wagner ahead 54-41 at 14:50. Porter's 3-pointer closed out the run. Peeples' dunk pulled the Knights to 54-47 at 12:55, but Wagner responded with a 14-4 run to take control. Matt Vitale capped the burst with a layup.
